instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The orchestration follows the ISO 23247 Reference Architecture, mapping each software component (FEs) to a dedicated ROS 2 package containing one or more ROS 2 nodes. The Physical Twin Entity hosts general vehicle functions such as Point Cloud Clustering & Tracking, while the Digital Twin Entity manages data storage, pre‑processing, and control mechanisms. The User Entity contains the User Interface FE split into 3D Visualization and Control Panel sub‑components. Deployment on separate hardware facilitates dedicated resource management per entity, with ROS 2’s data‑distribution service handling inter‑entity messaging and synchronization."
]

instance dt_technical_connection : DTDFVocab:TechnicalConnection [
    base:desc "All intra‑DTS software components communicate over a ROS2 network, which utilizes DDS for publish/subscribe messaging. Inter‑entity communication (between the Physical Twin Entity and the Digital Twin Entity) is conducted over a Wi‑Fi network using UDP at the transport layer, as illustrated in Fig. 2. The Data Translation FE serves as the serialization hub, synchronizing and converting sensor streams to comply with ISO 23247. The architecture forms a bus‑like topology within the vehicle, with all processing units exchanging data via DDS topics routed over the vehicle’s internal Wi‑Fi."
]

instance standardization : DTDFVocab:Standardization [
